staggers
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number: 1
Definition:[used elsewhere but commonly in spring and autumn in NZ] a specific disorder in which sheep and cattle have an unsteady gait [ usually caused by imbalance of magnesium in fresh lush pasture.]
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Flag: Farm Words
Domain:Rural
